rines, and the saints' role in the calendar, literature, and art.The book explores the central role played by the bodies and body parts of saints, and the special treatment these relics received. From the routes, dangers, and rewards of pilgrimage, to the saints' impact on everyday life, Bartlett's account is an unmatched examination of an important and intriguing part of the religious life of the past-as well as the present.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Mai 2019) 0aChristian martyrsxHistory. 0aChristian saintsxHistory. 0aChurch historyyMiddle Ages, 600-1500. 0aChurch historyyPrimitive and early church, ca. 30-600. 7aHISTORY / Medieval.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781400848782423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781400848782.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG  aPDA9PRIN